{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1155af1f-b22f-4c85-aca5-b82ab5db57af","content":"\n\nHere's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.5.0\" />\n   ```\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Or migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it routes through MTP now.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you're on .NET 9+, you can also set `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` for the native MTP executable entry point.\n- The xUnit v2 MTP runner (`xunit.runner.mtp`) lets you stay on v2 APIs without a full v3 migration.\n\nWould you like help updating your `.csproj` file directly?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b1c78c23-6aaa-42a7-aa65-b140dfadd886","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":487},"id":"69c87eab-c232-43c5-8669-6fdd99244d0e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:31.231Z","parentId":"e8534a5f-bc36-473d-b02d-4bae03154d5b"}
